tamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Ginkgo 6000 mg Tebonin® EGb761® Size Size 30 tablets Blackmores Ginkgo 6000 mg (Tebonin® EGb 761®) contains a proprietary extract of Ginkgo biloba. It is used to support memory recall, support cognitive function, and support healthy blood circulation. This one-a-day formula also provides antioxidant support to reduce free radicals formed in the body. Taken daily, it offers convenient support for individuals looking to maintain cognitive health and circulation. With a high-strength dose in a single tablet, it is suitable for ongoing daily use. Good health changes everything—start with Blackmores Ginkgo 6000 mg. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Brain Health Memory Circulation No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Supports cognitive and mental function. Maintains memory and mental recall. May assist with healthy blood circulation. Contains a proprietary, extract of ginkgo biloba standardised to flavonglycosides and terpene lactose. The effects of ginkgo biloba may take 4-6 weeks to appear. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy; or if taking blood thinner medication (e.g. warfarin), talk to your doctor before use. Discontinue at least 2 weeks before elective surgery. Do not use if you have any allergy to ginkgo biloba or any ingredients in this product. This product may cause headache and mild gut disturbance. If you develop any adverse symptoms, stop use and seek immediate medical attention. If symptoms persist, change or worsen talk to your health professional If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Contains lactose and sugar. Benefits Dosage Warnings Supports cognitive and mental function. Maintains memory and mental recall. May assist with healthy blood circulation. Contains a proprietary, extract of ginkgo biloba standardised to flavonglycosides and terpene lactose. The effects of ginkgo biloba may take 4-6 weeks to appear. Adults Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy; or if taking blood thinner medication (e.g. warfarin), talk to your doctor before use. Discontinue at least 2 weeks before elective surgery. Do not use if you have any allergy to ginkgo biloba or any ingredients in this product. This product may cause headache and mild gut disturbance. If you develop any adverse symptoms, stop use and seek immediate medical attention. If symptoms persist, change or worsen talk to your health professional If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Contains lactose and sugar. Ingredients Active i