Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Tailormade blend of essential vitamins and minerals for men. Specifically formulated with ‘Sustained Release Technology’ to provide lasting energy for up to 8 hours a day. Supports immune system function. Supports energy production. Supports testosterone levels. Supports mental function. Supports healthy sexual function and reproductive system health. Supports general health and wellbeing. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING - If you are pregnant, or considering becoming pregnant, do not take vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 microgram retinol equivalents for women & 900 microgram for men. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. This product contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 mcg for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Tailormade blend of essential vitamins and minerals for men. Specifically formulated with ‘Sustained Release Technology’ to provide lasting energy for up to 8 hours a day. Supports immune system function. Supports energy production. Supports testosterone levels. Supports mental function. Supports healthy sexual function and reproductive system health. Supports general health and wellbeing. Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING - If you are pregnant, or considering becoming pregnant, do not take vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 microgram retinol equivalents for women & 900 microgram for men. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. This product contains selenium which is toxic in high doses. A daily dose of 150 mcg for adults of selenium from dietary supplements should not be exceeded. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Thiamine nitrate 1.5 mg equivalent thiamine (vitamin B1) 1.2 mg Riboflavin (vitamin B2) 1.3 mg Nicotinamide 16 mg Calcium pantothenate 6.5 mg equivalent pantothenic acid (vitamin B5) 6 mg Pyridoxine hydrochloride 1.6 mg equivalent pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 1.3 mg Folic acid (vitamin B9) 400 micrograms Cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) 2.4 micrograms Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 45 mg Biotin 30 micrograms Calcium carbonate 250 mg equivalent calcium 100 mg Chromium picolinate 282 micrograms equivalent chromium 35 micrograms Colecalciferol 5 micrograms equivalent vitamin D3 200 IU Cupric sulfate pentahydrate 3.3 mg equivalent copper 850 micrograms d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 12.3 mg equivalent vitamin E 14.9 IU Ferrous fumarate 15.7 mg equivalent iron 5 mg Heavy magnesium oxide 87.5 mg equivalent magnesium 50 mg Lycopene 2 mg Manganese sulfate monohydrate 10.8 mg equivalent mangan