ncy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy, heart conditions; or if taking blood thinner medication like warfarin, talk to your doctor before use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. This product may have a laxative effect. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Benefits Dosage Warnings Supports learning and information processing. Supports memory recall. Maintains cognitive function including learning, memory and attention. Contains standardised extracts of ginkgo and bacopa herbal extracts. Adults Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. x Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy, heart conditions; or if taking blood thinner medication like warfarin, talk to your doctor before use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. This product may have a laxative effect. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Ginkgo biloba (ginkgo) extract dry conc. 60 mg equivalent dry leaf 3000 mg (3 g) standardised to ginkgo flavonglycosides 16.02 mg standardised to ginkgolides & bilobalide 4.02 mg Bacopa monnieri (brahmi) extract dry conc. 150 mg equivalent dry whole plant 3000 mg (3 g) standardised to bacosides 67.5 mg Ginkgo Brahmi Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach