om taking more than 3 g / day of phytosterols from all sources. Not for the treatment of high cholesterol. Blood cholesterol levels should be regularly checked. If you have pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Helps reduce intestinal absorption of cholesterol from dietary sources. Helps maintains healthy cholesterol. Maintains general health and wellbeing. Plant sterols are natural compounds produced by plants that have a similar structure and function to the cholesterol found in our bodies. Supplies betacarotene which may be depleted when taking phytosterols. Adults Take 1 capsule two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. There is no benefit from taking more than 3 g / day of phytosterols from all sources. Not for the treatment of high cholesterol. Blood cholesterol levels should be regularly checked. If you have pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per capsule: Vegetable oil phytosterol esters (plant sterols) 1000 mg (1 g) Dunaliella salina extract soft conc. 5 mg standardised to betacarotene 1.5 mg Cholesterol Health® Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Black