on. Supports eye health. Antioxidant to reduce free radicals in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet once a day or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING - Contains zinc, which may be dangerous if taken in large amounts or for a long period of time. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Helps support eye macula health. Supports healthy vision. Supports eye health. Antioxidant to reduce free radicals in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Adults Take 1 tablet once a day or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING - Contains zinc, which may be dangerous if taken in large amounts or for a long period of time. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 250 mg d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 165 mg equivalent vitamin E 200 IU Zinc oxide 49.8 mg equivalent zinc 40 mg Cupric oxide 1.3 mg equivalent copper 1 mg Macu-Vision® Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability A