  ('e917f516-a496-46fb-9119-92df1a19421e'::uuid, 'manual', 'TH', null, 'Blackmores Kaloba®', 'blackmores_kaloba', '40e4806a-5049-4668-8d29-ab36a31202dd'::uuid, 'blackmores', 'blackmores', 'https://images.contentstack.io/v3/assets/blt948bd74310fc0ad0/blt93c5c7e433138b86/68bfb91a66de316ea729e6b7/9300807274996-1.webp', 'https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/kaloba', 'https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/kaloba', 'Blackmores Kaloba® is clinically proven for the treatment of acute bronchitis and acute sinusitis symptoms.', null, 'Blackmores Kaloba®', null, 'Blackmores Kaloba® is clinically proven for the treatment of acute bronchitis and acute sinusitis symptoms.', null, null, null, 'https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/kaloba', '{"dosage":"for use. Read the","locale":"en","parser":"blackmores_structured_ingredients_v2","titleEn":"Blackmores Kaloba®","htmlLength":163136,"validation":{"status":"failed","reasons":["no_canonical_match","no_dosed_facts"],"summary":"No usable per-serving product facts.","checkedAt":"2026-05-22T00:31:47.755Z","matchableFactCount":0},"description":"Blackmores Kaloba® is clinically proven for the treatment of acute bronchitis and acute sinusitis symptoms.","descriptionEn":"Blackmores Kaloba® is clinically proven for the treatment of acute bronchitis and acute sinusitis symptoms.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Kaloba Oral Liquid All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Kaloba® Size Size 50 ml Good health changes everything - support recovery of respiratory symptoms associated with acute bronchitis and acute sinusitis with Blackmores Kaloba®. This clinically studied oral liquid contains Pelargonium sidoides, a traditional herbal medicine used to relieve symptoms of acute bronchitis and sinusitis. Kaloba® helps reduce the severity and duration of symptoms and improves recovery time in both adults and children. The convenient drop-dosing format makes it easy to take, and it&#x27;s suitable for family members aged 2 years and over. Kaloba® is well-tolerated and offers a natural option for managing respiratory symptoms. Always read the label and follow usage guidance. Product Format Liquid Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Respiratory Health Sinusitis No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Helps reduce recovery time and symptoms of acute bronchitis For the treatment of acute sinusitis. Features children&#x27;s doses* for acute bronchitis Well-tolerated and suitable for family members over 2 years old with acute bronchitis*. Convenient drop dosage. AUST-R registered complementary medicine. *Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with a doctor. Dosage Acute bronchitis Adults and adolescents over the age of 12 years - Take 30 drops (1.35 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 6-12 years - Take 20 drops (0.9 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 2-5 years - Give 10 drops (0.45 mL) 3 times a day. Acute sinusitis Adults - Take 60 drops (2.7 ml) 3 times a day. The correct dosage can be taken straight from a spoon or mixed with half a glass of water. The entire contents of the glass should be drink straight away. Take one dose in the morning, midday and evening. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Consult a doctor immediately if the condition does not improve within one week, in case of fever lasting for several days or in case of shortness of breath or if you cough up bloody sputum. Kaloba® should not be used in children under 2 years of age. Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with your doctor. Use during pregnancy or breast feeding is not recommended without first consulting with your doctor or pharmacist. Treatment duration should not exceed 1 week for acute bronchitis and 3 weeks for acute sinusitis. Contains 12% alcohol. Benefits Dosage Warnings Helps reduce recovery time and symptoms of acute bronchitis For the treatment of acute sinusitis. Features children&#x27;s doses* for acute bronchitis Well-tolerated and suitable for family members over 2 years old with acute bronchitis*. Convenient drop dosage. AUST-R registered complementary medicine. *Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with a doctor. Acute bronchitis Adults and adolescents over the age of 12 years - Take 30 drops (1.35 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 6-12 years - Take 20 drops (0.9 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 2-5 years - Give 10 drops (0.45 mL) 3 times a day. Acute sinusitis Adults - Take 60 drops (2.7 ml) 3 times a day. The correct dosage can be taken straight from a spoon or mixed with half a glass of water. The entire contents of the glass should be drink straight away. Take one dose in the morning, midday and evening. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Consult a doctor immediately if the condition does not improve within one week, in case of fever lasting for several days or in case of shortness of breath or if you cough up bloody sputum. Kaloba® should not be used in children under 2 years of age. Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with your doctor. Use during pregnancy or breast feeding is not recommended without first consulting with your doctor or pharmacist. Treatment duration should not exceed 1 week for acute bronchitis and 3 weeks for acute sinusitis. Contains 12% alcohol. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per 1mL oral liquid: Pelargonium sidoides (pelargonium) liquid extract 821 mg equivalent dry root 91 mg Kaloba® Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam In