ree radical damage to the body cells. Dosage Adults Take one tablet 1 to 2 times a day with meals or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow directions for use. Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Suitable for use during pregnancy and breastfeeding. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Benefits Dosage Warnings Maintains vitamin C levels in the body Supports immune system health. Reduces the severity and duration of common colds symptoms. Supports collagen formation. An antioxidant helping to reduce free radical damage to the body cells. Adults Take one tablet 1 to 2 times a day with meals or as prescribed by a health professional. Children under 18 years Only as prescribed by a health professional. Always read the label and follow directions for use. Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Suitable for use during pregnancy and breastfeeding. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 500 mg Vitamin C 500 Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Herita