ow the directions for use. WARNING: If you are pregnant or considering becoming pregnant, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, Vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol equivalents for men. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites and soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Maintains healthy eye function. Maintains healthy vision. Assists night vision. Supports skin health. Supports immune system health. Maintains mucous membrane health which is the first line of defence against infections. Convenient one-a-day formula. Easy-to-swallow capsule. Adults Take 1 capsule a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING: If you are pregnant or considering becoming pregnant, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, Vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol equivalents for men. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites and soya bean products. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per capsule: Retinyl palmitate 2.75 mg equivalent vitamin A 5000 IU 1500 micrograms retinol equivalents Vitami